description: A seafood market sells scallops , mussels , and oysters in packages named seafood medley one and seafood medley two . A package of seafood medley one contains 20 grams of scallops , 30 grams of mussels , and 50 grams of oysters . A package of seafood medley two contains 40 grams of scallops , 40 grams of mussels , and 20 grams of oysters . The market has available 10000 grams of scallops , 12000 grams of mussels , and 11000 grams of oysters . If the profit per package of seafood medley one is $ 20 and the profit per package of seafood medley two is $ 25 , how many of each should be sold to maximize profit ?
